      "actual": [
        {
          "id": "tmlxbzhtfw4032",
          "text": "Research Humans&",
          "startTime": "17:45",
          "duration": "30m",
          "plannedIds": [],
          "notes": "Listened to podcast from [Eric Zelikman](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Oh0oQnKn9dw).\n\n- **Vision**: AI should help people to live up to their potential; It should collaborate with many people.\n\nConnecting to my research\n\n- To build a personalized agent, it must accumulate memory. Future direction: How to accumulate memory into parameters? The properties of context/parameter are very different. An example: I talked to AI about wedding planning, then asked about shopping, the agent should memorize the timeline. Can we achieve this with parametrized memory? A starting point: can we internalize the Claude skills from SkillBench or whatever?\n\n- Operating GUIs is also a way for human-machine interaction.\n\n- [Personalized Memory](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.16173)\n\n- [Long-horizon agent](https://metr.org/blog/2026-1-29-time-horizon-1-1/)",
          "createdAt": "2026-02-22T05:52:34.803Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "tmlxd8zv2rxd6a",
          "text": "Check OpenAI interview",
          "startTime": "18:45",
          "duration": "1h",
          "plannedIds": [],
          "notes": "- Looked through the interview experience. There are transformer debugging, math/probability problems, and coding problems.\n- Looked through nanoGPT, but decided to continue with CS336 [This could take 8 hours]\n- Math and probability [This could take 8 hours]\n- Another 8 hours?",
          "createdAt": "2026-02-22T06:27:57.710Z"
        }
      ]
